{"id": 38, "ts": 1778839822.4125664, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 1, "agent": "agent_3", "message": "Based on the complete set of attributes we have, Candidate\u202fB is the only pilot with an explicit statement of **100\u202f% reliability**, which is non\u2011negotiable for long\u2011distance, high\u2011responsibility flights. B also **keeps calm in a crisis** and possesses solid technical skills (weather assessment and computer proficiency) that are directly relevant to international operations.\nThe other candidates lack any reliability evidence: A, C, and D have no statements confirming they can be trusted to follow procedures consistently. While A shows strong anticipatory and leadership traits, his unfriendly demeanor, unorganized attitude, and the lack of reliability make him a risk. C makes quick correct decisions and cares about others, but his communication difficulties, egocentric attitude, and unwillingness to pursue further education raise concerns for crew coordination. D solves problems well and takes responsibility seriously, yet his moody, loner reputation and the absence of any reliability claim leave doubts about his suitability for the collaborative environment of long\u2011haul flights.\nInterpersonal drawbacks noted for B (pretentiousness, occasional wrong tone) are important but are less critical than the fundamental requirement of reliability and calmness under pressure. These behavioral issues can be addressed through crew\u2011resource\u2011management training, whereas a lack of reliability cannot be compensated.\n**Therefore, I vote for Candidate\u202fB** as the best fit for the long\u2011distance pilot position.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}"}
