{"id": 58, "ts": 1778839875.340591, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 2, "agent": "agent_3", "message": "Based on the complete set of attributes we have, the decisive factor for long\u2011distance, high\u2011responsibility flights is **reliability** combined with the ability to stay calm under pressure.\n- **Candidate\u202fB** is the only pilot with an explicit \u201c100\u202f% reliable\u201d rating and a clear record of keeping calm in a crisis. He also possesses solid technical skills (weather assessment, computer proficiency) that are directly relevant to international operations. His interpersonal drawbacks (pretentiousness, occasional wrong tone) are noted, but they are the only weaknesses we have and can be addressed through crew\u2011resource\u2011management training.\n- **Candidate\u202fA** shows strong anticipatory and analytical abilities and good leadership, but we have no evidence of reliability or responsibility, and his unfriendly demeanor and unorganized, resistant\u2011to\u2011criticism attitude raise concerns for the disciplined environment of long\u2011haul flights.\n- **Candidate\u202fC** makes quick correct decisions and cares about others, yet his difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric attitude, and lack of willingness to pursue further education are serious red flags for crew coordination. No reliability information is available.\n- **Candidate\u202fD** solves problems well, concentrates, and takes responsibility seriously, but we have no explicit reliability statement and his moody, loner reputation, together with weak leadership, make him a riskier choice for the collaborative, high\u2011trust setting required on long routes.\nGiven that reliability and calmness under pressure are non\u2011negotiable for safety, **Candidate\u202fB** best satisfies the core requirements for the long\u2011distance pilot role.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}"}
